Section 1:
Act 754 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: S3/20/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 SENATE BILL 487
4
5 By: Senator Irvin
6 By: Representative L. Johnson
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW ON THE DESTRUCTION OR
10 EXPUNGEMENT OF JUVENILE DELINQUENCY RECORDS; AND FOR
11 OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 TO AMEND THE LAW ON THE DESTRUCTION OR
16 EXPUNGEMENT OF JUVENILE DELINQUENCY
17 RECORDS.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 9-27-309(b), concerning expungement of
22 delinquency adjudications under the Arkansas Juvenile Code of 1989, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24 (b)(1)(A) Records of delinquency adjudications for a felony involving
25 violence as defined under § 5-4-501 shall be kept for ten (10) years after
26 the last adjudication of delinquency or the date of a plea of guilty or nolo
27 contendere or a finding of guilt as an adult.
28 (B) Thereafter they may be expunged.
29 (2) Records of all other delinquency adjudications shall be
30 expunged upon the individual's twenty-first birthday.
31 (2)(3) The court may expunge other juvenile records at any time
32 and shall expunge all the records of a juvenile upon his or her twenty-first
33 birthday, in other types of delinquency, dependency-neglect, or families in
34 need of services cases.
35 (3)(4) For purposes of this section, “expunge” means to destroy
36 seal as defined in § 16-90-1404.
*LJH202*
